            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Meta requires at least $1/day per ad set, but realistic results typically need $10-20/day minimum. Lead and conversion campaigns should budget $20-50/day to generate enough conversion events for Meta's algorithm to exit the learning phase.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the difference between Meta Ads Manager and boosting a post?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Boosting a post is a simplified promotion with limited targeting and objectives. Ads Manager gives you full targeting capability (custom audiences, lookalikes), all six campaign objectives, advanced creative options, and detailed performance reporting including conversion tracking.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How long does it take for Meta ads to show results?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Most campaigns exit the learning phase after approximately 50 optimization events, which typically takes 3-7 days depending on budget and audience size. During the learning phase, performance is unstable — avoid making changes until the phase completes.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Can you run Instagram ads without Facebook in Meta Ads Manager?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Full Ads Manager access requires a connected Facebook Page. You can boost Instagram posts directly within the Instagram app with limited targeting, but for proper Instagram advertising with audience targeting and conversion tracking, Ads Manager is required.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

